\pard\f0\fs28 Tubers globose. Cauline leaves present. Perianth-segments erecto-patent or somewhat convergent, but not forming a distinct galea. Labellum conspicuously 3-lobed, slightly longer than the other perianth-segments; spur absent. Viscidia distinct; bursicle very rudimentary.
