\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. H. monorchis} (L.) R. Br. in Aiton,{\i  Hort. Kew}. ed. 2, {\b 5}: 191 (1813). Tuber solitary at anthesis, 2-4 others appearing later on slender, underground stolons. Plant 7-25 cm. Lower leaves 2-3(-4), 20-70 × 3-10 mm, elliptic-oblong to linear-lanceolate, the upper 1-2, linear-subulate, bract-like. Spike 1·5-9 cm, slender, sometimes secund, usually rather lax. Flowers yellowish-green, honey-scented. Outer perianth-segments 2·5-3 mm, ovate-lanceolate, obtuse, the inner c. 3·5 mm, oblong-lanceolate, often shallowly lobed near base. Labellum 3·5-4 mm; lobes oblong, the 2 lateral projecting at right angles or curved forwards, much shorter than the middle. 2n = 40. {\i Grassland. Much of Europe, but absent from the extreme north and most of the Mediterranean region and the south-west.} Au Be Br Bu Cz Da Fe Ga Ge He Ho †Hu It Ju No Po Rm Rs (N, B, C, W, E) Su.
