\pard\f0\fs28\qc  {\b 12.      Neottianthe}        Schlechter
\par

\pard\f0\fs24\qc  D.A. Webb. 
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Tubers usually ellipsoid. Basal leaves 2. Perianth-segments more or less equal, connivent into a galea. Labellum deeply 3-lobed, densely papillose. Spur conical, curved, shorter than ovary, directed downwards and forwards. Viscidia close together, above the stigma; bursicles absent.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. N. cucullata} (L.) Schlechter,{\i  Feddes Repert.}{\b  16}: 292 (1919) ({\i Gymnadenia cucullata} (L.) L. C. M. Richard). Tubers ellipsoid to subglobose, sometimes emarginate or shortly 2-lobed. Plant 10-30 cm, glabrous. Basal leaves 5-7 × 1·5-3 cm, elliptical; cauline leaves 1-2, small and bract-like. Spike 3-8 cm, secund, rather lax. Flowers lilac-pink. Perianth-segments 6-8 × 1-1·5 mm, acuminate. Labellum 7-9 mm, somewhat deflexed; lateral lobes linear-setaceous; middle lobe longer, linear-oblong. Spur c. 5 mm, slightly dilated at apex.{\i  Damp woods and mountain meadows. U.S.S.R. and Poland, from} c. 57°{\i  N. in Latvia and C. Ural southwards to} 49° 30'{\i  N. in W. Ukraine.} Po Rs (B, C, W).
