\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. P. chlorantha} (Custer) Reichenb. in Moessler,{\i  Handb.} ed. 2,{\b  2}: 1565 (1828) ({\i Orchis montana} auct., vix F. W. Schmidt). Like {\b 1} but flowers more strongly tinged with green, less fragrant, and with slightly larger perianth-segments; spur 18-27 mm, slightly dilated at apex; anther-cells convergent above but widely separated below. 2n = 42.{\i  Woods, meadows and damp heaths. Much of Europe, but absent from parts of the north, east and south-west.} All except Az Bl Cr Fa Is Lu Rs (N, E) Sa Sb.
