\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 3. P. micrantha} (Hochst.) Schlechter,{\i  Feddes Repert.}{\b  16}: 378 (1920). Tubers 2, ovoid-ellipsoid. Plant 20-50 cm. Lowest 2 leaves 6-15(-17) × 2-6·5 cm, oblanceolate-oblong to elliptical, usually one distinctly above the other but rarely subopposite; above them 2-6 much smaller leaves passing into the bracts. Spike 8-13 cm; flowers green. Perianth-segments 2-4 mm. Labellum 2-4 mm, narrowly oblong to oblong-elliptical, horizontal. Spur 2·5-8 mm, obtuse, 1/3-4/5 as long as ovary.{\i  Mountain grassland. • Açores.} Az.
