\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 5. P. obtusata} (Pursh) Lindley, {\i op. cit.} 284 (1835). Roots cord-like, fleshy but scarcely tuberous. Plant 6-20 cm. Foliage leaf solitary, basal, 4-6 × 1·5-2 cm, elliptical, tapered to a sheathing base which is largely enclosed in a hyaline sheath representing a second basal leaf; a third leaf, small and bract-like, is present on upper part of stem. Spike short, rather dense; flowers 3-6, greenish-white. Perianth-segments 2-3 mm. Labellum 3-3·5 mm, rhombic-lanceolate, horizontal or somewhat deflexed. Spur 2·5-3 mm, curved, half as long as ovary. 2n = 126. {\i Calcareous}
